x4freetext: PHOTONUCLEAR REACTIONS IN MEDIUM WEIGHT NUCLEI V-51,
MN-55, AND CU.

x4codes.hlp: Inst. Fiziki A.N. Armenian SSR, Jerevan, Union of Soviet Socialist Republics

x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Nuclear Physics, Section A, Vol.285, p.482 (1977)

x4codes.hlp: Inst. Fiziki A.N. Armenian SSR, Jerevan, Union of Soviet Socialist Republics

x4freetext: STATISTICAL ERRORS GIVEN.
SYSTEMATIC ERRORS AMOUNTED TO 15%.
NEW RESULTS ON THE PHOTOSPALLATION OF THE MEDIUM WEIGH
NUCLEI 51V, 55MN AND CU AT BREMSSTRAHLUNG END-POINT
ENERGY BETWEEN 2 AND 5 GEV ARE PRESENTED. THE YIELDS
OF RESIDUAL NUCLEI WERE MEASURED BY THE ACTIVATION
METHOD USING A GE(LI) DETECTOR.
THE RESULTS ARE ANALYZED WITH THE EMPIRICAL RUDSTAM
FORMULA AND COMPARED WITH DATA OBTAINED IN LOWER
ENERGY PHOTON PROTON INDUCED REACTIONS.
BY AUTHORS. DATA WERE PUBLISHED IN FORM OF
TABLES.
CORRECTED BY V.VARLAMOV, V.MCLANE.
CORRECTED BY V.VARLAMOV.
JOURNAL CODE IN REFERENCE OF SUBENT 1 CHANGED,
ISOMER=0 FLAGS INSTEAD OF BLANK USED FOR PARTIAL
CROSS SECTION DATA FOR THE ELEMENT GROUND STATES.
